review:
first of all, obvious problems:
- you "stick" to the boss during combat, and he carries you around the whole arena during attack. you are guaranteed to find yourself cornered at the end;
- locked-in camera can't keep up with boss movement, and he is often located partially off-screen;
- when boss flies into space, you get the worm's POV and only see his ass, not the incoming attack. the camera only rises to 50 degrees or smth;
- you better turn off camera shake and motion blur. otherwise any incoming attack is a pixelated mess;
- talent descriptions are very uninformative. you need to watch an hour of youtube guides to learn basic game mechanics;

now that's what i call [b]TikTok Combat[/b]

all opponents are divided into dummies and well-developed opponents.

if the boss is anything special, you have two ways to kill him:
- you can create a special invisible-oneshot-crit-immobilizer-running-charged-smash-gourd build, or your monkey gang can simply remove the boss - whatever trash u want;
- you can fight the way the developers intended – pure melee combat.

If you are about to get the best possible experience from the fight, your only options are:
1) read the guide on the boss's phases and transitions;
2) watch ongbal 0.2x speed video to understand the timings;
3) record your own 0.2x speed video to understand the timings;
4) make 10-30 attempts to memorize the moveset;
5) now you're ready to counter with all perfect dodges or sees-throughs rather than tank the boss with your face.

there is NO WEAPON PARRY in the game that would break the boss poise - you should strike with 3+ focus heavies. charging a 3+ heavy is immediately punished! you need to insert it into a light combo and perform a see-through. your attacks have different durations and LOCK you in animations - you CAN'T INSTANTLY interrupt them! taking damage STUNS you and cancels the use of abilities/items! enemies feint, hold animations and perform lightning-fast attacks.

you must know the enemy's behavior in advance and remember which attacks you can follow with your combos! you CAN'T use the WHOLE MARTIAL ARSENAL on the first try - you'll only be using the first lights and dodges! as a result you either beat the boss with a stick and didn't get the expirience, or you learned the boss but lost all the interest. now you just follow the schedule. moreover you will never encounter this boss again (as an ordinary enemy for example). 

i’m not making shorts with phonk backgrounds. i'm not promoting myself with only-parry-no-parry-steering-wheel videos. i just want to try all the stances, all the abilities and complete the game with full experience. in all other respects the game is flawless. 

that's the main problem with chinese games coming out now: they make you play action RPGs like multiplayer competitive fighting games.
